The microstructural and morphological characterization of the
as-fabricated carbon networks were conducted by field-emis-
sion scanning electron microscopy (FE-SEM, S-4800, Hitachi)
and transmission electron microscopy (TEM, FEI, Tecnai G
F30). X-ray powder diffraction (XRD, X’Pert Pro, Philips),
Raman spectroscopy (Jobin–Yvon Horiba, HR800) and X-ray
analyses were carried out to determine the chemical structure
The electrochemical properties of the carbon networks were
studied with a CR2032-type coin cell. The details of the cell
assembly can be found in previous works [11,29]. The galvano-
static discharge–charge cycling and rate tests of the cells were
measured using a Neware BTS-610 multichannel battery tester
at room temperature. Cyclic voltammetry measurements were
performed over a potential window of 0.02–3.00 V vs Li/Li
